# Remove columns we will not be using
oil = oil.drop(columns=['DATAFLOW', 'LAST UPDATE', 'freq', 'siec', 'partner', 'unit', 'OBS_FLAG'])
gas = gas.drop(columns=['DATAFLOW','LAST UPDATE', 'freq', 'siec', 'partner', 'unit', 'OBS_FLAG', 'TIME_PERIOD', 'geo'])
coal = coal.drop(columns=['DATAFLOW','LAST UPDATE', 'freq', 'siec', 'partner', 'unit', 'OBS_FLAG', 'TIME_PERIOD', 'geo'])
renewables = renewables.drop(columns=['DATAFLOW','LAST UPDATE', 'freq', 'nrg_bal', 'unit', 'OBS_FLAG'])

#Rename columns to make easier to udnerstand
oil = oil.rename(columns={"OBS_VALUE" : "Oil", "geo": "Country", "TIME_PERIOD": "Year"})
gas = gas.rename(columns={"OBS_VALUE" : "Natural_Gas"})
coal = coal.rename(columns={"OBS_VALUE" : "Solid_Fossil_Fuels"})
renewables = renewables.rename(columns={"OBS_VALUE" : "renewable", "geo": "Country", "TIME_PERIOD": "Year"})

# combine dataframes
total = pd.concat([oil, gas, coal], axis=1, join="inner")
total = pd.merge(total, renewables, how='left')

# remove non-EU nations
total = total.loc[(total["Country"] == "BE") | (total["Country"] == "BG") |

# Check how EU Oil, Natual Gas, and Solid Fossil Fuels imports from Russia have changed over time
eu = total.loc[total["Country"] == "European Union"]
for (columnName, columnData) in eu.items():
    if (columnName == "Oil") | (columnName == "Natural_Gas") | (columnName == "Solid_Fossil_Fuels"):
        eu.plot.line(x="Year", y=columnName, xlabel="Year", ylabel=columnName, title="EU Imports of Russian " + columnName + " Across Time", grid=True)
In [5]:
# Compare the Total Energy Imports from Russia vs. % of Renewables in Energy Sector in each country compare acros time 
countries = np.unique(total['Country'])
for country in countries:
    single = total.drop(total[country != total['Country']].index)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,5))
    ax2 = ax.twinx()
    ax.set_title("Total Energy Imports from Russia vs. % of Renewables in Energy Sector in " + country + " Across Time")
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    lns1 = ax.plot(single['Year'], single['total_imports'], color='blue', label= 'Total Energy Imports from Russia (per Btu)')
    lns2 = ax2.plot(single['Year'], single['renewable'], color='green', label='% of Renewables in Energy Sector')
    ax.set_ylabel('Total Energy Imports from Russia (per thousand tonnes)')
    ax2.set_ylabel('% of Renewables in Energy Sector')
    lns = lns1+lns2
    labs = [l.get_label() for l in lns]
    ax.legend(lns, labs, loc=0)
    ax.grid()
    plt.show()
